<subSubSection id="D53E93B6FE1C9AE7A119A9D2439B7798" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="94C59C52DD2D6E6680AA3D2357C50CC1" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C52A22A202BF68BED7FABD5A0CFC243" pageId="4" pageNumber="111">
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="14D91C2EDB7DA6B17377ABC7DCBDA324" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus bipunctatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatus">Bambusananus bipunctatus</taxonomicName>
(Li, 1999) in general appearance, but can be distinguished by: pygofer in lateral view with ventral margin broadly smoothly rounded, without notch at base of ventral process (with notch in 
<taxonomicName id="7BC51B2D7A17306307A3B89D07A955D8" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus bipunctatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatus">Bambusananus bipunctatus</taxonomicName>
); connective with stem slightly shorter than arms (longer in 
<taxonomicName id="3CB6333614AB33B7DF3CDDE6C9D4B000" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus bipunctatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatus">Bambusananus bipunctatus</taxonomicName>
); aedeagal shaft with appendages longer, in lateral view with apex reaching to middle of aedeagus (in 
<taxonomicName id="32F3B5C337D0F9BD30CC9896BF1E02C7" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus bipunctatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatus">Bambusananus bipunctatus</taxonomicName>
, appendages shorter and apex only reaching to apical one-fifth of aedeagus). This new species is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="278C19C2BE19E5FFD48D4CD6DCFD6CC9" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus lii" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">Bambusananus lii</taxonomicName>
(McKamey &amp; Hicks, 2007), but can be distinguished by: upper area of frontoclypeus with a large kidney-shaped black marking (lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="A136AE6CA3268C1BF8F90D267BE5BE97" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus lii" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">Bambusananus lii</taxonomicName>
); ventral margin of pygoger without any lobe (with a lobe near middle in 
<taxonomicName id="9AD1F5F2F4A096656096AFD6C920BEC7" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus lii" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">Bambusananus lii</taxonomicName>
); appendages of aedeagal shaft mostly straight basally, apex directed laterally (elbow-like and curved basally, apex directed caudad in 
<taxonomicName id="35AF44FE4634EAABDDEA6FCBA621DAA1" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus lii" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">Bambusananus lii</taxonomicName>
); ventral margin of aedeagus without any teeth (with a row of teeth at middle in 
<taxonomicName id="BC8484094D78BA0702AD95A63A479054" authority="Li &amp; Xing, 2011" authorityName="Li &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bambusananus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bambusananus lii" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">Bambusananus lii</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
